4.09/5  rDev -7.9%look: 4 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4Consumed 2/23/17
A: Tangerine gold with some orange at the core and honey around the edges - even more turbid and hazy than the average Trillium hop soup - pours with a medium sized, white head, fades to a few wisps, leaves some streaks of lacing
S: Juicy, obviously - lots of citrus, with some orange and grapefruit juice, zest - herbal, leafy, a touch grassy, dank - spicy - some sharp lime - earthy - damp pineapple - pear and apple - some light sweetness, pale malts
T: Sharp, bright citrus - orange and a lot of grapefruit - citrus juice, zest, pith - bright lime, maybe a touch of lemon - herbal with some grassy notes, spicy green hops, a bit woodsy -  not getting as much pineapple as in the aroma - some underripe peach, melon rind - moderately herbal - above-average bitterness - some light bread, pale malts at the base
M: Medium body, medium carbonation, smooth, sharper finish than most of the DDH Trillium beers
O: 2 Scales 2 Furious
Double dry hopped Trillium beers are consistently interesting, at the very least. Not all are better than their "single dry hopped" counterparts. Maybe I am not in love with DDH Scaled because I don't seem to love big amounts of El Dorado  in Trillium. Still, it's definitely worth a try. 1,242 charactersangrybabboon, Feb 23, 2017
