4.25/5  rDev -4.3%look: 3.75 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.25Had this on 2016-09-16 in Columbia, PA from a 16oz can dated 2016-09-06 so it is very fresh.
A - Very-cloudy golden-orange with a 1-finger white head that fades quickly leaving moderate lace. 
S - Fresh pineapple, papaya, navel orange, pine needles, more floral than dank.
T - More hop forward than the smell indicates.  Nice burst of gooey hob bud flavor and bitterness before the big fruit flavors kick in with pineapple, orange, apricot and watermelon.  There's a light biscuit flavor with just a hint of caramel.  Big pine flavor too with some earthy spice and woody accents.  Finishes with a sharp bitterness with grass, tea and pepper accents.  
M - Medium body and light-medium carbonation.  Resinous, prickly and finishes dry. 
O - A flavor bomb.  Only knock for me is I'd have liked a bit more fruit sweetness in the finish to counter the lingering bitterness.  I prefer their normal Scaled for this reason. 921 charactersTucquan, Sep 24, 2016
