4.08/5  rDev -8.1%look: 3.5 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25Service:	Can
Bottled on: Aug-2-2016
A:	
Pours a hazy almost mountain-dew-like color that is turbid as could be with a finger or so of soapy head that evaporates to nothing immediately.  No retention; no lacing.  (3.5)	
S:	
Candied citrus with a whiff of ethanol; lemon drops, mandarins, some pine sap, vodka.  (4.25)	
T:	
Dry, slightly resinous hop bitterness that kind of sticks to the palate.  There is a little citrus sweetness but nothing like the nose.  (4)	
M:	
Medium body, active carbonation, almost-fluffy feel in the mouth, lingering "resinousness".  (4)	
O:	
Decent dry-hopped IPA from Trillium.  
This is definitely not my favorite I have had from them, but it is far from being a mess.  For starters it is the first I've had where I would agree with people who say that they (turbid IPAs) are not visually appealing.  The nose is delicious. Like a yellow dum-dum dipped in everclear.  The boozy part I could do without, but otherwise the aroma is very appealing.  The flavor is dominated by a flat, even bitterness that doesn't seem too much like the aroma.  It is pretty drinkable and pretty tasty all told, though.  Would have again, though if I had the option I'd choose one of their other beers (not to sound entitled or anything).  Still, a kickass IPA, to be sure. (4.25) 1,299 charactersTheDoctor, Aug 07, 2016
