4.7/5  rDev +5.9%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75This beer pours a nice hazy yellow straw color with a nice white head. The smell is fantastic. Tropical citrus, pineapple. The flavor is just as great as the smell is. Lots of citrus and pineapple with a hint of melon at the finish. Mouthfeel is very nice. Overall this is an amazing beer which I will try to get again. 319 charactersDirtyDawg10, Jun 08, 2016
4.53/5  rDev +2%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.5The base beer was great, and adding El Dorado and Citra this should be fantastic! 5/24/16, quite fresh.
Pours a nice creamy fluffy foamy 1 finger head that fades at a med pace, nice frothy lacing, typical super murky milk-shake honey blond tan color.
Nose is as expected, loads of citrus, big juicy orange juice, pineapple, some grapefruit pith, no real rind bitterness, a touch of tropical like almost mango, nice creamy base malt, with juicy orange flesh and tangerine, a little orange sugar candy. 
Taste brings more of hte same, so much orange flesh out front, like biting into an orange with plenty of pith in there, a juicy tangerine, even some lemon, just explosions of citrus, with some nice tropical notes, a big pineapple, touch resin and some mango skin, with fair bitterness. Nice creamy malt base, a little juicy malt taste, a little touch of booze warmth. Hops start to turn grassy floral and a bit earthy later, actually an interesting earthy mossy flavor in there from out of nowhere late, drier finish, a little sticky, big citrus orange juice and pith lingering.
Mouth is med to fuller bod a bit chewy, nice creamy, popping bubble zesty carbonation, just about no booze.
Overall an awesome IPA, maybe not quite as good as I was reaching for, but I was reaching really high since I had such an incredible IPA yesterday, this was def way up there though, a delicious IPA I will sip and enjoy all the way to the end, and then wish I had more. 1,462 charactersjlindros, Jun 08, 2016
