4.04/5  rDev -9%look: 3.75 | smell: 4 | taste: 4 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4750ml bottle, stamped with what appears to be 05.24.16, poured into a Trillium snifter glass.
The beer pours a ridiculously murky orange color, hues of tan and gold, intensely cloudy and turbid with a firm, white head, good retention and plenty of spotted lace. The aroma is really intense with sweet citrus juice, a bit of tangy lime as well with some wildflower, honey, strong pale wheat and graininess that lingers nicely, tame bitterness, but really just a ton of juiciness. The flavors echo the nose well, loads of juicy citrus, orange and tangerine at first with bitter grapefruit peel, some pine and earthiness creeps out behind it before a bit of a floral note and some strong wheat flavors take over offering some sweetness to counteract the bitter hoppiness, while the lingering flavor is tart lime juice. The mouthfeel is good, coating, full bodied with gentle carbonation and a very smooth texture and a dry kick at the finish that isn't too abrasive. 
Verdict: A nice IPA from Trillium, not my favorite combination of hops, but plenty of stuff to like here. Not the most complex IPA and it feels a bit muddled rather than layered, but this was a very nice beer for a warm June evening. 1,200 characterskevanb, Jun 07, 2016
