4.49/5  rDev +1.1%look: 4.75 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.25Bottle purchased at Trillium Brewing Company in Boston, MA.
This one pours a turbid, soft-looking and bright orange, with a 1.5 inch head, and a lot of lacing.
Smells likejust insanely juicy and sweet tangerine and orange marmalade, with some very slight grassiness and grapefruit.
Like much of Trillium's lineup, this is just straight up hoppy fruit juice. There's so much candied tangerine, orange rind, slight grassiness, grapefruit and overripe peach. It's unbelievably juicy, as is to be expected.
This is medium bodied, fairly thick but not quite as thick as Trillium's other mega IPAs, which is fine. It's got a really juicy mouthfeel.
Another banger from Trillium. 677 charactersGreesyFizeek, Feb 10, 2016
